-- Israel Stocks: Israel Petrochemical, Nova Are Active
-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 2012-02-20T11:14:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-20/israel-stocks-israel-petrochemical-nova-are-active.html
Israel ’s  TA-25 index  advanced for a
second day, gaining 0.3 percent to 1,115.14 at 12:30 p.m. in Tel
Aviv.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Israel Petrochemical Enterprises Ltd. (PTCH)   headed for
the biggest gain since Feb. 1, increasing 4.6 percent to 7.595
shekels. The maker of raw materials for the plastic industry
said it’s in talks with the Bereshit fund for a 120 million
shekels ($32 million) loan.  Nova Measuring Instruments Ltd. (NVMI)   fell for a third
day declining 1.3 percent to 31.86 shekels. The maker of
monitoring systems for the semiconductor manufacturing industry
said fourth-quarter net income dropped to $4.97 million from
$7.49 million in the year-earlier period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
